OL,3,CStarmer faces final Cabinet and PMQs
OL,4,Cas Burnham edges closer to No 10
OL,6,FThe Prime Minister said: "I leave on
OL,7,FMonday. I leave with good grace, I
OL,8,Fleave very pleased with what we've
OL,9,Fbeen able to achieve in government in
OL,10,Fthe two years that I've had the
OL,11,Fprivilege of being prime minister.
OL,13,F"I'm pleased to have delivered on the
OL,14,Fpromises that I made to many people in
OL,15,Fthis garden, and I'll make this last
OL,16,Fpromise, which is I will stand with
OL,17,Fyou and walk with you for as long as
OL,18,FI've got breath in my body."
OL,26,@nD@ZOUuD@AOUzD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
